guard against recursive data structures in pruneFunctions. fixes #14
guard against recursive data structures in pruneFunctions. fixes #14
fixed broken doctest.

Merge pull request #11 from jmandel/master

Normalize channel origin to lower-case (with test case)
normalize channel origin to lower-case (with test case)
minor code formatting fixes for consistency.
added section on notifications to docs.
Added link to docs.
Separated test running infrastructure into run-tests.js and CSS into main.css.
Fixed a bug whereby all collapsed sections aren't expanded when doctests fail.
Refined docs on channel constructor.
Added github ribbon and touched up docs.
renamed test directory to docs.
Added more documentation.
created collapsible 'more' sections that contained more detailed information about specific functionality.
remove example prompts from final successful output and syntax highlight the doctest examples.
Added syntax highlighting using the shjs syntax highlighting library.
converted all doctests to script snippets instead of pre tags.

Fixed a TODO so that we're now using a jschannel to get script source code from the child frame instead of poking into the iframe, which doesn't work on chrome file: URLs or IE8. Also added a HTML doctype so pre-wrap works on IE8.

It's now possible to put doctest script code in a <script> tag in a pre.doctest element, contained in a function definition (so the code isn't actually executed on page load). This is done for a number of reasons, including but not limited to:

* it makes it easy to copy/paste actual code to/from the doctest source code without having to manually insert or remove $ and > prompts.

* because we're now looking at raw source and inserting the $ and > prompts ourselves, we can perform further transformations on the raw source, such as syntax highlighting.

* syntax errors thrown by the code contain proper line number information.

* code editors like textmate can properly syntax highlight the doctest snippets.
Fixed tests to work on MSIE8.
CSS prettification and removal of unused rules.
Only do the readability improvements on doctest code if all the doctests pass, to ease debugging of failing doctests.
Replace wait() in documentation with 'Time passes...' boxes after doctests are finished.
More improvements to documentation/doctests.
Refactored some doctests to make them easier to read.
Fixed a bug from my last commit, added a todo, and another doctest.
Preliminary timeout implementation. See the end of the doctest page for example. Right now this duplicates a bit of code from another part of the thing, which I am not super happy with.
Tests auto-start on page load. Removed one test b/c it's now rendered irrelevant.
Displaying some of the parent frame JS code now, to make the doctests easier to understand.
Added jquery to test page and simplified some JS with it.
Made the doctest testing page look a bit nicer.
Added 'use strict' to the JSChannel closure, since all the tests pass with it turned on. Hopefully this will not prove to be an unfortunate idea.

Define 'Channel' using 'var' instead of forcing it to be a global. This allows jschannel.js to be compiled into a closure and e.g. included in a bookmarklet and other kinds of scripts that want private access to JSChannel without polluting the global scope.
Various minor typo fixes and clarifications.

Merge pull request #9 from brianlovesdata/master

Allow chaining with bind
Return channel object from bind to allow chaining.

This is a somewhat experimental change that attempts to make the doctests easier to understand by displaying relevant snippets of code from the child frame.

I'm not sure how effective it is, but it does help me understand how to use jschannel a bit better by juxtaposing child and parent code on the same page.

This enhancement is purely for the sake of readability, however, and shouldn't impact the execution of tests in any way.

Made the doctests easier to read by changing some of the examples to be multi-line. Among other things, this makes it so readers don't have to scroll horizontally in the <pre> areas to see all the code.
Typo string fix, 'non-existant' -> 'nonexistent'
Another typo fix.
More trivial comment typos, its -> it's
Trivial comment typo, its -> it's
windows can't be object keys.  duh.  fix previous commit.
use window to disambiguate window destinations, which now allows multiple child iframes bound to different children with the same scope and origin
more portable array checking, and invoke callbacks in global scope (thanks ianb)

invoke a success callback with no arguments when the
                  payload is 'undefined'
allow js 'undefined' as a response payload
rough cut of documentation for the protocol employed by JSChannel
add .origin property to the transaction object, useful for when '*' is bound to know who it is you're talking to
fix typo resulting in exception in the case when origin is something other than '*'.  oops

move from one message handler per active channel to a single handler that does routing.  This means we only parse a message once, and msg dispatching is log(n) as opposed to exponential.  Also some restrictions are lifted, and others are made explicit (throw rather than just break).  I'm hoping this is a Good Change.
whitespace changes
add .DS_Store to .gitignore files
a little pile of pages useful for performance testing

break tranTbl into two - incoming requests, and outgoing requests.  This reduces the size of hash tables when we do lookups, and eliminates the possible problem that could occur if an incoming and outgoing request shared the same id at the same time.
make the thrown error message about absense of JSON handling more accurate
document message types and how you can tell them apart
there is now a global transaction ID counter to ensure all queries emmitted from a single javascript context will have a unique id, and to allow eminent perf optimizations
minor restructuring to make room for static data - shared between channel instances
two more IE8 fixes, doctestjs is broken for multiline tests on IE,  and there's some odd scoping assymetry
port to IE8
update to latest (working) doctest
a little json parsing for less capable browsers
fix tests under safari, who likes to append debugging information in the form of properties to objects that you throw
port all tests to new doctestjs, with much more concise usage
merge a fix for broken ellipse parsing in doctestjs
bump to latest doctestjs
impelment an .onReady callback that the client can attach to to be informed when the channel is 'ready', that is we've completed the application level handshake and know the other side is there
catch and log exceptions from observers, but don't let them muck up message handling
change name of query function to 'call'
pass gotMessageObserver a clone of incoming messages before any manipulations are performed
full support for message payloads that consist wholey of falsey values, like 0, false, or 'null'.  Closes #3.
don't add a .callbacks property to messages when no callbacks exist.  Closes #1.
build now takes a configuration object. debug output to console is off by default, but may be configured on.  Add observer hooks for before messages are posted and after they're received.  Closes #2.
jschannel now automagically converts URLs into origins, tests updated as stuff that used to fail now succeeds
make the example in the readme simpler
implement the 'destroy' function for cleaning up channels
for debugging purposes, each channel has a 'channel id' which lets you understand where messages are coming from
implement unbind
explicitly disallow establishment of a channel where both endpoints are in the same window... for now.
update license
prune excessive debug messages, clean up comments
I'm proud of big
move test button to top of page
lots and lots of test
fix typo which was preventing objects from properly being converted into error messages
implement first couple tests of argument validation in .build() call
add a fix to doctestjs for graceful recovery when we fail to parse stack traces.  submitted upstream here: http://github.com/ianb/doctestjs/pull/1
implement first couple tests of argument validation in .build() call
copy in doctestjs library and give credit to the nimble and fair author.
wordsmithing
firefox port
